Sunday Aborisade, Abuja President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, on Tuesday, swore in a former governor of Bayelsa State, Seriake Dickson, to represent Bayelsa West Senatorial District in the National Assembly. Others who were also sworn in were Cleopas Moses (PDP – Bayelsa Central); Nora Ladi Daduut (APC – Plateau South); and Adetokunbo Abiru (APC – Lagos East). The lawmakers were sworn in at exactly 11.04am shortly after the commencement of the plenary. Two of the newly sworn in lawmakers, Nora Ladi Daduut and Adetokunbo Abiru replaced the Late Senators Bayo Osinowo; and Ignatius Longjan who represented Lagos East and Plateau South before their demise in 2019 and 2020, respectively. Dickson, who addressed journalists after he was sworn in, noted that almost all the senators were his friends, having served in the House of Representatives. He said, “We will join our colleagues to work for our people. There are several battles to be fought for the good of our people. “I will work with stakeholders to see how we can stabilise our country which is going through defective structure and imbalances. “We also have the challenges of working towards enhancing development in Bayelsa.” Abiru on his part, pledged to partner with his colleagues to tackle the problems in the country, especially the issue of insecurity and job creation. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com   